<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>US Sizes </strong>: Typically use numerical values for women (e=
.g., 0, 2, 4) and waist measurements for men (e.g., 30, 32, 34).</li>



<li><strong>UK Sizes </strong>: Similar to US sizes but often differ slight=
ly in numeric values.</li>



<li><strong>EU Sizes </strong>: Use larger numbers (e.g., 36, 38, 40) and a=
re based on body measurements.</li>



<li><strong>Japanese Sizes </strong>: Often smaller than Western sizes and =
use unique labels like =E2=80=9CS,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CM,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CL=
,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CLL,=E2=80=9D etc.</li>
</ul>



<p>These differences make it challenging to find the right size when shoppi=
